snippet.textDisplay:
such a shame that Crownie wouldnt just give this one game of Rekkles adc vs the god Peyz. Rekkles clearly wanted this and it seems that it was agreed in the team beforehand else the facecams wouldnt have been in this line up. 
Rekkles himself was somewhat of an Idol as adc, a true legend. He didnt change role because he couldnt cut it on ad anymore but because he descovred that there is a level (mostly embraced by asians but not only) that made him humble and learn to embrace the beauty of a beast support next to you fighting to keep you alive and well. Who didnt have that league experience where you played botlane for some reason and you had that golden chemistry with your support. Imagine Crownie was just willing to do that as probably discussed and gift Rekkles this experience against a godly ad in Peyz and Keria against u,m. This is basically the opportunity of a life time; at your peak gameplay, you get to face the maybe best players in the legacy of this yearsold game on your lane. This was like judgment day - see how good you truly are against the best there is. Seems like Crownie wasnt willing to give that up. Subcounsciously ofc :) our thought go rarely further then our breakfeast in reality, i know.
